@startuml ProbationClassification_DatabaseFlow
title Probation Classification - Database Flow

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam handwritten false
skinparam databaseBackgroundColor #E8F5E9
skinparam databaseBorderColor #4CAF50
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
skinparam noteBorderColor #FBC02D
skinparam activityBackgroundColor #E3F2FD
skinparam activityBorderColor #1976D2

|Service Layer|
start
:JobRun(batchSize);

note right
  **Do-While Loop - Pagination Loop**:
  Uses system parameters for progress tracking
  Continue until all probation customers processed
end note

repeat
  :Start();
  note right
    Initialize ProbationModel
  end note

  |DataAccess Layer|
  :GetProbationCustForScanning(batchSize);
  
  |CTS_DataCenter (MySQL)|
  :Execute SP: **CTS_DC_CustClassification_ProbationScan_Get**;
  note right
    **Database**: CTS_DataCenter.ctsService
    **Timeout**: 300 seconds (5 minutes)
    
    **Purpose**: Get customers in probation period
    **Input**: @ip_NoOfRecord (batch size)
    **Output Parameters**:
    - @op_LastCustID (long) - Last processed CustID
    - @op_LastCategoryID (int) - Last processed CategoryID
    
    **Returns**: ProbationEntity[]
    - CustId (long)
    - SportGroupId (int)
    
    **Query Logic**:
    ```sql
    SELECT TOP @ip_NoOfRecord
      CustID,
      SportGroupID
    FROM CTSCustomerClassification
    WHERE ProbationEndDate > NOW()
      AND CustID > @LastCustID  -- From system parameter
    ORDER BY CustID, CategoryID
    ```
    
    **Pagination**:
    - Start from LastCustID (system parameter)
    - Order by CustID, CategoryID
    - Return last processed IDs for next batch
    
    **System Parameters Used**:
    - DailyProbation_LastCustID (input)
    - DailyProbation_LastCategoryID (input)
  end note

  :Return ProbationEntity[] + LastCustID + LastCategoryID;
  
  |Service Layer|
  :Store ProbationModel;
  note right
    **ProbationModel Contents**:
    - CustProbations (ProbationEntity[])
    - LastCustID (for pagination)
    - LastCategoryID (for pagination)
  end note

  if (Has probation customers?) then (yes)
    :ClassifyProbation();
    note right
      Convert CustIDs to comma-separated string
      Ex: "123456,789012,345678"
    end note

    |DataAccess Layer|
    :ClassifyProbation(custToString);
    
    |bodb_VR2Model (SQL Server)|
    :Execute SP: **CTS_GeneralNormalClassification_Probation_Preprocess**;
    note right
      **Database**: bodb_VR2Model.wsv_cts
      **Timeout**: 300 seconds (5 minutes)
      
      **Purpose**: Re-classify probation customers
      **Input**: Customer list (comma-separated string)
      
      **Processing Steps**:
      
      1. **Parse Input**:
         - Split comma-separated CustIDs
         - Create temp table #ProbationCustomers
      
      2. **Get Probation Performance**:
         ```sql
         SELECT 
           c.CustID,
           c.ProbationStartDate,
           c.ProbationEndDate,
           c.CurrentCategoryID,
           SUM(t.TurnoverRM) AS TurnoverDuringProbation,
           SUM(t.WinlossRM) AS WinlossDuringProbation,
           COUNT(t.BetID) AS BetCountDuringProbation,
           COUNT(DISTINCT t.BetDate) AS ActiveDaysDuringProbation
         FROM CTSCustomerClassification c
         JOIN CustomerTransaction t ON c.CustID = t.CustID
         WHERE c.CustID IN (#ProbationCustomers)
           AND t.TransactionDate BETWEEN c.ProbationStartDate AND NOW()
         GROUP BY c.CustID
         ```
      
      3. **Determine Category Change**:
         **Improvement (Downgrade)**:
         - PA + Improved → PotentialPA
         - PA + Significantly Improved → Normal
         - PotentialPA + Improved → Normal
         
         **Deterioration (Upgrade)**:
         - PotentialPA + Worse → PA
         - Normal + Worse → PotentialPA
         
         **Maintenance**:
         - No significant change → Keep current category
         - Extend probation if still PA/PotentialPA
      
      4. **Apply Re-Classification Rules**:
         - Thresholds for improvement/deterioration
         - Based on turnover, winloss, bet patterns
         - Consider sport-specific rules
      
      5. **Update Classification**:
         ```sql
         UPDATE CTSCustomerClassification
         SET 
           CategoryID = @NewCategoryID,
           CategoryName = @NewCategoryName,
           ProbationEndDate = CASE 
             WHEN @NewCategoryID IN (PA, PotentialPA) 
             THEN DATEADD(DAY, 30, NOW())  -- Extend
             ELSE NULL  -- Complete probation
           END,
           UpdatedDate = NOW()
         WHERE CustID IN (#ProbationCustomers)
         ```
      
      6. **Log Changes**:
         - Record category changes
         - Track probation outcomes
         - Performance metrics
      
      **Re-Classification Matrix**:
      | Current | Performance | New Category |
      |---------|-------------|--------------|
      | PA | Much better | Normal |
      | PA | Better | PotentialPA |
      | PA | Same/Worse | PA (extend) |
      | PotentialPA | Better | Normal |
      | PotentialPA | Worse | PA |
      | PotentialPA | Same | PotentialPA (extend) |
    end note

    :Return void;
  else (no)
    note right
      No probation customers to process
    end note
  endif

  |Service Layer|
  :UpdateLastScanDate();
  
  |System Parameters|
  :Update DailyProbation_LastCustID;
  |CTS_DataCenter (MySQL)|
  :UPDATE SystemParameter;
  note right
    **Update Query**:
    ```sql
    UPDATE CTS_SystemParameter
    SET Value = @LastCustID,
        UpdatedDate = NOW()
    WHERE ParameterKey = 'DailyProbation_LastCustID'
    ```
    
    **Purpose**: Track progress for next batch
    **Enables**: Resumable processing
  end note

  |System Parameters|
  :Update DailyProbation_LastCategoryID;
  |CTS_DataCenter (MySQL)|
  :UPDATE SystemParameter;
  note right
    **Update Query**:
    ```sql
    UPDATE CTS_SystemParameter
    SET Value = @LastCategoryID,
        UpdatedDate = NOW()
    WHERE ParameterKey = 'DailyProbation_LastCategoryID'
    ```
    
    **Purpose**: Secondary pagination key
  end note

  |Service Layer|
  :Check if more customers exist;
  note right
    **isContinue Logic**:
    - true: CustProbations.Any() = more to process
    - false: CustProbations is empty = all done
    
    **Return**: bool (isContinue)
  end note

repeat while (isContinue = true?) is (yes)
-> no;

|Service Layer|
:Complete;
note right
  **Job Completion**:
  - All probation customers processed
  - System parameters at final position
  - Ready for next job run (starts from LastCustID)
  
  **Next Job Run**:
  - Resets LastCustID and LastCategoryID to 0
  - Starts from beginning
  - Processes new probation customers
end note

note right
  **Database Architecture**:
  
  **CTS_DataCenter (MySQL)**:
  - CTSCustomerClassification (probation data)
  - CTS_SystemParameter (pagination tracking)
  - Read-heavy operations
  
  **bodb_VR2Model (SQL Server)**:
  - CustomerTransaction (betting data)
  - BetDetails (bet information)
  - Complex calculations and joins
  - Re-classification logic
  
  **Pagination Mechanism**:
  1. System parameters store progress
  2. Each batch updates LastCustID/LastCategoryID
  3. Next batch starts from last position
  4. No risk of re-processing
  5. Survives job interruptions
  
  **Performance Considerations**:
  - Batch size: 5000-10000 customers
  - Timeout: 300 seconds per SP
  - Indexed on CustID, ProbationEndDate
  - Efficient pagination with ORDER BY
  
  **Re-Classification Logic**:
  - Based on probation performance
  - Compares before vs during probation
  - Determines improvement/deterioration
  - Updates category accordingly
  - Extends/completes probation
end note

stop

@enduml

